																		What I want to see happen with my SCPs
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eric-h" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(474585); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=474585&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227343" alt="eric_h" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=474585)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eric-h" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(474585); return false;" >eric_h</a></span> <span class="odate time_1318444423 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Oct 2011 18:33</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1279818">
									

<p>Re: 699, someone (GrandEnder, was that you?) added a good bit about 699-1 slinking around, with the lights and cameras failing in its presence, so no one actually sees it. What I'd like to see happen at the end (this may be better for part 3) is the reverse of the escape &#8212; the camera fails again in the research bay, and when it's back on, 699 is closed, and once again we can't open it (or even see the mechanism by which it opened for the escape). Apparently, we are not actually containing 699-1 &#8212; rather, it has infiltrated us and is waiting for something &#8212; something that didn't happen during the incident, so it went back in the box. The box is keeping us from experimenting on it or getting rid of it, and is actually for 699-1's benefit, not the Foundation's. I'll probably update <a href="/scp-699">SCP-699</a> to reflect all of this.</p>
<p>As for Dr. Clarkson wandering around with 911, I want to do some kind of face-off with 343. Not sure how it will play out yet&#8230;</p>

							</div>

