			<div class="content" id="post-content-1295813">
									

<p>I just put a first draft of a 699 story in my sandbox: <a href="http://scpsandboxwiki.wikidot.com/eric-h-s-sandbox">http://scpsandboxwiki.wikidot.com/eric-h-s-sandbox</a></p>
<p>The premise(s):</p>
<p>699 was not sent by a future version of the Foundation. Rather, it was sent by a future MC &amp; D. Dark, specifically, since he is the one in MC &amp; D who actually has a significant amount of paranormal knowledge/power (quite a lot, in fact). Dark prefers to stay out of day-to-day operations and research/experiment, and everyone else is equally pleased not to see him. If there ever was a person who just gives everyone the creeps, it's Dark&#8230; Most of MC &amp; D's operatives have not seen Dark in years; they even think he might be dead. Not so. Dark knows pretty much everything MC &amp; D is involved with, and he is NOT happy with the events following Tempest Night. From his point of view, practically everything in Site 17 should be in MC &amp; D's hands by now&#8230;maybe it's time for him to oversee this particular operation personally?</p>
<p>I'd really like to see the other folks here who have been writing MC &amp; D stuff edit the story and elaborate on it. PM me here if you'd like to talk about it&#8230;</p>

